    <PrimAttribute name="allocationAttribute" id="d7416e95-d7e5-40fc-a63e-ac5961753086">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <text>
The CM_QueryProperty: allocationAttribute is the link between query properties and allocation properties.

JMT has query properties for the item selector and separate properties for allocations (yard, voyage, invoice etc).

If you are adding a new item selector query property and you are also adding that property to yard allocations; 
you should set the 'allocationAttribute' on the CM_QueryProperty to be the yard allocation global constant. e.g.

        create tmpProp as CM_QStringProperty persistent;
        tmpProp.set('Booking', CM_TrackedItem::bookingReference.name, self.className);
        tmpProp.allocationAttribute := YACriteriaType_BookingRef;
		
This would be in the method CM_QDefTrackedItem::createProperties which is run at every upgrade.


SEE THIS WIKI LINK ON WHAT TO DO IF SETTING THIS:

https://wiki.cnw.co.nz/JMT-KB-Adding/ResetingSelectorQueries-ToBeCompleted#preview




</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
